httpserver can take three arguments:
	-p [port]	some int for the port number.
	-r [root]	some folder to serve files out of. default=document_root
	-t [title]	some title for the default (404) response page.

example:
	make
	sudo ./httpserver -p 80 -t 'Welcome to httpserver! Here was your request...'

- Schell
